chapter:
Description of the ALFS profile syntax


ALFS profiles are written using an XLM syntax. This chapter describes
the various XML elements that can occurs in the profile.


For each element, one describes :




the formal definition of the element, using the DTD syntax




a description of the element




one or several examples




the equivalent bash scripts for the examples, when applicable






The bash scripts have been generated by YAALFS. The checking
of the return code have been removed.



This document describes the syntax of the version 3.0 of
the syntax, as used in nALFS 1.1.2 and YAALFS.




